ocket%20motor%20to%20boost%20the%20missile%20to%20supersonic%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20booster%20ultimately%20burns%20out%2C%20outside%20air%20enters%20the%20combustion%20chamber%20through%20a%20port%20at%20the%20front%20of%20Stinger's%20solid%20fuel%20rocket%20motor%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20stored%20on%20board%2C%20and%20ignites%20the%20ramjet%20fuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ramjet%20cycle%20thus%20greatly%20increases%20the%20engine's%20delivered%20performance%20and%20ultimately%20the%20missile's%20range%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Army%20center%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat'll%20help%20soldiers%20use%20Stinger%20to%20engage%20with%20threats%20like%20uncrewed%20aerial%20systems%20with%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20capabilities%20at%20longer%20distances%2C%20said%20Capability%20Area%20Lead%20for%20Air%20and%20Missile%20Defense%20John%20Gibbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20Red%20Wasp%2C%20we%20can%20reach%20out%20and%20touch%20them%20at%20greater%20distances%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225770%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20servicemen%20search%20for%20a%20target%20with%20an%20FIM-92%20Stinger%20launcher%20on%20the%20front%20line%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20in%20May%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d425bf585f1dff88b22659%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223847%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20servicemen%20search%20for%20a%20target%20with%20an%20FIM-92%20Stinger%20launcher%20on%20the%20front%20line%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20in%20May%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAndriy%20Andriyenko%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStingers%2C%20man-portable%20air%20defense%20systems%20that%20fire%20surface-to-air%20missiles%2C%20have%20been%20in%20service%20since%201981%2C%20with%20few%20changes%20to%20their%20range%20over%20the%20past%20almost%2045%20years.%20They're%20fired%20over-the-shoulder%20and%20hone%20in%20on%20their%20target%20via%20infrared%2C%20making%20soldiers%20and%20insurgents%20more%20effective%20against%20helicopter%20gunships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERed%20Wasp%20was%20a%20high-risk%2C%20high-reward%2C%20completely%20government-owned%20program%20to%20make%20the%20system%20much%20more%20lethal%2C%20Chappell%20Ray%2C%20deputy%20capability%20area%20lead%20for%20air%20and%20missile%20defense%2C%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Stinger%20was%20chosen%20as%20a%20candidate%20for%20testing%20this%20type%20of%20technology%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20industry%20propulsion%20experts%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20feasibility%20of%20applying%20solid%20fuel%20ramjet%20technology%20to%20the%20Stinger%20form%20factor%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibbs%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20team%20took%20that%20as%20a%20challenge%20and%20within%2018%20months%2C%20successfully%20demonstrated%20the%20concept%20in%20a%20flight%20test.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditional%20flight%20testing%20is%20expected%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStingers%20have%20been%20used%20in%20combat%20for%20decades.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20US%20made%20the%20uneasy%20decision%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F32-year-anniversary-of-first-stinger-missile-use-in-afghanistan-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshare%20the%20missile%20with%20US-backed%20Afghan%20rebels%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20erode%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20control%20of%20the%20air.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war%2C%20an%20estimated%202%2C000%20and%202%2C500%20were%20sent.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EStingers%20have%20also%20seen%20combat%20in%20other%20wars%2C%20most%20recently%20Ukraine.%20Weeks%20after%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20then-US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresident-biden-send-stinger-missiles-ukraine-shoot-russian-helicopters-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5